<exploration xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="PA-3-3">
  <p>
    Let <m>f(x) = 2 + \frac{3}{1+(x+1)^2}</m>.
    <ol label="a.">
      <li>
        <p>
          Determine all of the critical numbers of <m>f</m>.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Construct a first derivative sign chart for <m>f</m> and thus determine all intervals on which <m>f</m> is increasing or decreasing.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Does <m>f</m> have a global maximum?
          If so, why,
          and what is its value and where is the maximum attained?
          If not, explain why.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Determine <m>\lim_{x \to \infty} f(x)</m> and <m>\lim_{x \to -\infty} f(x)</m>.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Explain why <m>f(x) \gt 2</m> for every value of <m>x</m>.
        </p>
      </li>

      <li>
        <p>
          Does <m>f</m> have a global minimum?
          If so, why,
          and what is its value and where is the minimum attained?
          If not, explain why.
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </p>
</exploration>

